Additionally, the paper presents new data structures and algorithms for these problems, indicating that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of bit-packing techniques and recursion suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of the word RAM model, which is a common model in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's focus on improving query time and cost suggests that it may be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, specifically in the area of efficient algorithms.
